Cagiest | Alice Betterman 09-May-21 04:57 PM
“Why? Why did I do all this?” She says in a saddened voice. “Power, I did all the because of power. Humans have the potential to turn Earth into something that looks like it came out of a fantasy book, a world where everyone, humans and animals alike, can live together with no ill will towards anyone or anything, a world where people would say “it can only get better” and not “at least it’s not any worse”.” “But instead people use that potential, that power, to try to put themselves at the top of the totem pole of power of our own creation.” “I never wanted to be a humanitarian, my entire family were humanitarians, but it wasn’t something I would’ve chose for myself. The Alice you know is a lie, I’m not a happy-go-lucky, energetic, always hoping for the best person. I only act this way because I thought it would help...... help people realize that we can do better.” She unwraps her bandages, revealing a burned and scarred face, and a blind eye. “And that’s not even the worst part.” She starts pulling at the skin of her right arm, which comes off like a really long glove, revealing a prosthetic arm. “I was in a war-torn country, helping my family and their humanitarian team when I met a young boy. You could tell that he.... he could’ve been one of those people you hear about how they’re doing great things in the world, not just for themselves, but for everyone.” “But then..... he stepped on a land mind, he died instantly, I didn’t even know his name yet, and I got away with these. She gestures to her arm and face. “While I was recovering I realized something, sure helping the poor and and less fortunate is all well and good, but the world isn’t going to get better permanently unless you go to the heart of the problem.”
“And the heart of the problem is power, the people in power in the world are the people with the most potential to make the world better for everyone, not just themselves. But instead they sit on their golden thrones not caring about anyone or anything besides making themselves more rich and powerful, even if that means stepping on everyone else, sabotaging their enemies, or even going to war where thousands will die. They have never and will never care for anything else.” “Unfortunately, the way the world works doesn’t allow people who want to truly do good to become powerful, because in order to become powerful you have to use whatever power you currently have to improve yourself, not others. Even in the rare case that someone good has a level of power where they could start helping others, they can’t use it for good because all the other powerful people are working against them, because good for all doesn’t mean good for them.” “But what if someone had a form of power no one else did? That person would be able to do whatever they wanted more freely because no one else has what they have, and so can’t fight them as easily. That’s why I did this. With the revival machine I could become one of, if not the most powerful person in the world. I would be able to use that power to change the world for the better, so that no person would ever have to go through what the boy, me, or you all went through ever again.” “I probably sound crazy, but I think that this is something the world needs, a good person who wants to do good things in power. I’m sorry all this had to happen, but if it helps I’m planning on reviving all of the people that died here, I know it probably doesn’t though.”
